text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus multinervis is an Asian species of trees in the beech family. It is native to central and southern China (Provinces of Anhui, Fujian, Guangxi, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Shaanxi, and Sichuan).Quercus multinervis is a tree up to 12 meters tall. Leaves can be as much as 15.5 cm long.
